Michelle,

I don&#39;t think the local schools would allow a device that lets us &quot;speak to the dead&quot; on school grounds. Hell, most schools won&#39;t allow prayer. The Queen Mary is a large, steel faraday cage (no signals to very poor reception inside). The fluorescent lighting thing I don&#39;t understand because I record everyday under two of them. As I said before and it looks like I will have to keep saying it. It is the person not the device that will determine whether you are successful in this research. Any and all boxes are just a way of bringing the speech into audible reality, we are the medium. To argue over equipment or method is ridiculous.

Now if you are here to submit your research, learn from others research or are just interested in what is going on in research then by all means stay. If you are here as a promoter for anyone or anything please leave, we don&#39;t want the distraction. If you have a problem with an individual on this forum then keep it private in your email. If you feel threatened, intimidated or frightened by anyone here, email one of us moderators or Misty the owner and we will do what we can within the group (warning, expelling or banning).

Best Regards,

Frank R.

----- Original Message ----
From: babiarz3 &lt;babiarz3@...&gt;
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Sent: Friday, December 14, 2007 7:38:35 AM
Subject: [EVP-ITC] Re: My mistruths...














            Mike,

I don&#39;t know if he tried to hide the article or not. It may have been

a coincidence that it disappeared within hours of me posting what had

been said. It took me awhile but, I re-found it. I&#39;m going to assume

that if he really wanted it to completely disappear it would have.

Although, writers are funny about their works. 

His stating openly that he&#39;d like to bring it into schools... that&#39;s

plain crazy. All my thoughts on negativity aside, do you really think

schools and parents will allow someone to bring a spirit communication

device into the class? &quot;Alright kiddos, this morning I&#39;m going to let

you listen to the voice of your dead relatives and who ever else might

decide to speak. Oh, and by the way, sometimes they use profanity. But

don&#39;t be scared.&quot;

However, my point of contention remains the same. Children and high

school students should not be used as testing subjects. The attitude

of we&#39;ll &quot;see what happens&quot; is irresponsible at best.  

I do not know if Chris has tried the radio shack hack or not. I do

know that messages and emails are coming in stating no success. I do

not know the reasons for the lack of success. It could be as simple as

not hacking it correctly, lack of ability to hear the voices... It

could also just not work for everyone. I know that even REG has stated

here that she couldn&#39;t get reception on the Queen Mary in Long Beach

California nor in a radio station for C2C, for the mini-box and other

devices she has. That confuses me some but... Also, another researcher

claimed to be unable to use his device due to fluorescent lighting. 

It seems that the jury is still out. I&#39;m watching closely. I just hope

that the whole children and high school student thing is reconsidered.

They need to be old enough to make an informed educated decision on

whether or not they wish to be part of the testing group. 



--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups .com, &quot;M.A. Coletta (Mike)&quot;

&lt;michaelcoletta@ ...&gt; wrote:

&gt;

&gt; I listened to an internet radio show yesterday where Mr. Moran was a 

&gt; guest.  He spoke about sending his field researchers out with mini-

&gt; boxes to schools, nursing homes, colleges, etc.  He was very open 

&gt; about it on the show.  He advised the audience that he wanted to get 

&gt; opinions about the box from all walks of life.  I don&#39;t think this is 

&gt; something he is trying to hide...???

&gt; 

&gt; Many of us our researchers here, and I think we would love to have 

&gt; our experimental devices tested by others.  Speaking of that, did you 

&gt; ever ask Mr. Moon to try the Radio Shack Hack 12-469/mixer setup I 

&gt; put together?  I seem to recall asking you to ask him a while back.

&gt; 

&gt; I would like his opinion on how it works for him. I don&#39;t think he 

&gt; will melt or anything by using it...

&gt; 

&gt; - Mike

&gt; 

&gt; --- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups .com, &quot;babiarz3&quot; &lt;babiarz3@&gt; wrote:

&gt; &gt;

&gt; &gt; A few weeks ago I posted that Rick Moran had written an article

&gt; &gt; stating that children and high school students would be part of the

&gt; &gt; testing subjects of the mini-box. Later that day the article was

&gt; &gt; replaced with a different article about the mini-box. I was told 

&gt; that

&gt; &gt; I was stating mis truths. I wasn&#39;t. I finally was able to locate the

&gt; &gt; missing article. I&#39;m providing a link to the entire article along 

&gt; with

&gt; &gt; the statement regarding our children. If the link somehow becomes

&gt; &gt; unavailable, I have done a screen shot and will provide it to 

&gt; whoever

&gt; &gt; asks.

&gt; &gt; Believe me when I say that this isn&#39;t to cause or stir crap. I was

&gt; &gt; basically called a liar and this clears up that misconception. If I 

&gt; am

&gt; &gt; banned from this group for telling the truth, than so be it. 

&gt; &gt; 

&gt; &gt; &quot;...it was not the question of whether the phenomenon existed to 

&gt; begin

&gt; &gt; with, but rather what is the phenomenon.  That will require a good

&gt; &gt; deal more effort to explore and beginning in January we will be

&gt; &gt; undertaking test sessions all over north and east Texas as well as

&gt; &gt; other national locations with a wide variety of folks to see what

&gt; &gt; happens within the group dynamic.  The testing will include folks 

&gt; who

&gt; &gt; are both believers and non-believers, skeptics, critics, other

&gt; &gt; researchers, children, high school students, college and grad

&gt; &gt; students, and senior citizens to name a few categories.&quot;

&gt; &gt; 

&gt; &gt; http://www.asup- inc.org/pages/ editorial11- 29-07.html

&gt; &gt; 

&gt; &gt; Are you willing to &quot;see what happens&quot; with our children?

&gt; &gt;

